<title>USA: Third Kendall Square exec settles insider case.</title>
<headline>Third Kendall Square exec settles insider case.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1996-11-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>A former sales executive of Kendall Square Research Corp settled charges of insider trading, fraud and violations of federal accounting and reporting rules, the Securities and Exchange Commission said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The executive, Peter Appleton Jones, settled without admitting or denying the charges, the SEC said.</p>
<p>Two other executives of the company, chief executive Henry Burkhardt III and executive vice president Karl Wasserman, had settled similar charges when the case was filed in April. The two also neither denied nor admitted any wrongdoing.</p>
